PROJET DE DEVELOPPEMENT DE
            L'ELECTRICITE SONELGAZ

abstracts.cdata!:
The Power Project is part of the
            1974-1977 investment program of SONELGAZ and includes: (a)
            Gas turbine plants with a capacity of 120 MW at Algiers; two
            units of 40 MW each of the Bloufarik substation, and one 40
            MW unit at the Bab-ez Zouar substation; (b) A main dispatch
            center in SONELGAZ' new head office at Algiers, and
            district dispatch centers at Oran and Annaba; (c)
            Construction of three 220 kV substations, six 60 kV
            substations and one 90 kV substation; (d) Consulting
            services for reorganization, engineering, a tariff study for
            electricity, and a market/tariff study for gas.
